  "text": "(1−α)(1−αβ) α . As explained by [CITATION_1] , among others, this is the so-called 'New Keynesian Phillips Curve'. 22 In other words, the inflation rate today depends just on the discounted sum of the future expected marginal costs, as can be easily found by iterating (7) forward 22 In fact just assuming that the real marginal costs depend on output (mct = 1 φ yt) and substituting, one gets",
